WEBVTT

00:01.067 --> 00:02.483
[birds chirping]

00:02.567 --> 00:05.067
[laughs] Hey, everybody!
It's me, Mickey Mouse.

00:05.983 --> 00:08.233
Say, you wanna come inside my clubhouse?

00:10.817 --> 00:13.775
Well, all right! Let's go!

00:14.608 --> 00:15.900
[loon howls]

00:16.567 --> 00:18.900
[laughs] I almost forgot.

00:18.983 --> 00:20.608
To make the clubhouse appear,

00:20.692 --> 00:23.650
we get to say the magic words.

00:23.733 --> 00:27.108
Meeska, Mooska, Mickey Mouse!

00:27.775 --> 00:29.192
Say it with me.

00:29.275 --> 00:32.775
Meeska, Mooska, Mickey Mouse!

00:33.983 --> 00:38.983
[cheerful music playing]

00:39.067 --> 00:41.400
♪ M-I-C-K-E-Y ♪

00:41.483 --> 00:42.942
♪ M-O-U-S-E ♪

00:43.025 --> 00:44.067
That's me!

00:44.150 --> 00:46.567
♪ M-I-C-K-E-Y ♪

00:46.650 --> 00:49.108
♪ M-O-U-S-E ♪

00:51.275 --> 00:54.192
♪ It's the Mickey Mouse Clubhouse ♪

00:54.275 --> 00:56.442
♪ Come inside
It's fun inside ♪

00:56.525 --> 00:58.400
♪ It's the Mickey Mouse Clubhouse ♪

00:58.483 --> 00:59.900
[announcer] Roll call.

00:59.983 --> 01:01.483
-Donald!
-Present.

01:01.775 --> 01:03.233
-[announcer] Daisy!
-Here.

01:03.317 --> 01:04.900
-[announcer] Goofy!
-Here.

01:04.983 --> 01:06.358
-[announcer] Pluto!
-[barks]

01:06.442 --> 01:07.942
-[announcer] Minnie!
-[giggles] Here.

01:08.025 --> 01:09.900
-[announcer] Mickey!
-Right here.

01:11.567 --> 01:14.317
♪ It's the Mickey Mouse Clubhouse ♪

01:14.400 --> 01:16.983
♪ Come inside
It's fun inside ♪

01:17.067 --> 01:19.442
♪ M-I-C-K-E-Y ♪

01:19.525 --> 01:21.858
♪ M-O-U-S-E ♪

01:24.067 --> 01:26.608
[Mickey] It's the Mickey Mouse Clubhouse.

01:26.692 --> 01:30.775
[chuckles] "Donald... Jr."

01:31.817 --> 01:33.317
[bike bell rings]

01:35.775 --> 01:36.983
Hi, everybody!

01:37.317 --> 01:38.692
Welcome to the Clubhouse!

01:40.483 --> 01:42.317
Whoa! [chuckles]

01:45.483 --> 01:47.358
-Hi, Mickey!
-[barks]

01:47.442 --> 01:49.692
Hiya, Goofy! Pluto!

01:49.775 --> 01:52.983
Glad you could make it for
"Show Your Special Talent Day"!

01:53.067 --> 01:55.233
That's when our friends gather
at Mickey Park

01:55.317 --> 01:56.775
to show off their talents.

01:57.608 --> 01:58.608
[laughs]

01:59.108 --> 02:02.692
♪ There's gonna be
A little song, a little dance ♪

02:02.775 --> 02:05.275
♪ And magic hankies
In your pants ♪

02:06.733 --> 02:09.692
-So everybody say Hooray!
-[both] Hooray!

02:09.775 --> 02:13.567
♪ It's Show Your Special Talent Day ♪

02:13.942 --> 02:14.983
Oh!

02:15.858 --> 02:16.858
Hm?

02:16.942 --> 02:18.525
Oh, boy, Mickey!

02:18.608 --> 02:20.608
It's sure gonna be a fun day.

02:20.692 --> 02:23.442
I can't wait to show off
my new magic tricks!

02:26.567 --> 02:28.192
Hiya, everybody!

02:28.942 --> 02:30.025
Hiya, Donald.

02:30.317 --> 02:32.275
Oh, who's your little pal?

02:32.358 --> 02:34.483
Gosh, he looks ducky.

02:34.817 --> 02:36.525
Just like you, Donald.

02:36.858 --> 02:40.400
I think we should call him, uh, Donald Jr.

02:40.900 --> 02:42.150
[quacks]

02:42.650 --> 02:44.525
Hello, Donald Jr.!

02:45.275 --> 02:47.192
[quacks]

02:50.442 --> 02:51.858
[exclaiming]

02:52.067 --> 02:55.192
[laughs] He's funny... and cute, too!

02:55.275 --> 02:56.942
He sure is!

02:57.025 --> 03:01.150
When he grows up,
he's gonna be just like me.

03:01.233 --> 03:02.858
Yeah. [laughing]

03:03.358 --> 03:07.233
Say, are you doing something special
for "Show Your Special Talent Day"?

03:07.483 --> 03:10.608
Yep. We're gonna dance and sing!

03:10.858 --> 03:12.108
Watch this!

03:12.400 --> 03:13.983
Step, step.

03:14.067 --> 03:15.650
Step, step!

03:15.733 --> 03:18.358
Kick this way, kick that way!

03:18.442 --> 03:20.692
Spin and wiggle, wiggle, wiggle!

03:20.942 --> 03:22.192
[barks]

03:22.525 --> 03:26.567
Come on, Junior! Step, step, step, step!

03:27.858 --> 03:29.317
Oh, no!

03:29.400 --> 03:30.942
Oopsie ducky!

03:34.108 --> 03:38.150
Gee, I think Donald Jr.
might need a little more practice!

03:38.233 --> 03:39.608
Aw!

03:39.775 --> 03:42.067
Don't worry, fellas. We'll help you!

03:42.358 --> 03:45.192
Will you help Donald
and Donald Jr. practice

03:45.275 --> 03:47.942
their song and dance
for "Show Your Special Talent Day"?

03:49.817 --> 03:52.858
Great! Now let's go get some Mouseketools!

03:56.108 --> 03:58.400
♪ Mouseke-Hey, Mouseke-Hi
Mouseke-Ho ♪

03:58.858 --> 04:01.358
♪ Mouseke-Ready, Mouseke-Set,
Here we go! ♪

04:01.650 --> 04:04.025
♪ You're a thinking
And a solving work-it-througher ♪

04:04.567 --> 04:06.817
♪ Mouseke-Me, Mouseke-You
Mouseke-Doer ♪

04:07.358 --> 04:09.733
♪ Mouseke-Me Mouseke-You
Mouseke-Doer ♪

04:11.858 --> 04:12.900
[bell ringing]

04:13.025 --> 04:15.900
Oh, Toodles! It's time to get to it!
[laughs]

04:15.983 --> 04:18.067
Show us the Mouseketools to help us do it!

04:19.025 --> 04:23.150
Meeska, Mooska, Mouseke-Doer!

04:26.067 --> 04:30.400
Mouseketools, Mouseketools, Mouseketools!

04:30.483 --> 04:33.067
♪ Here are your Mouseketools ♪

04:33.692 --> 04:35.567
[Mickey] The Clubhouse rescue truck.

04:35.650 --> 04:37.442
Oh, it's got a fire hose!

04:39.692 --> 04:41.150
A ball of yarn!

04:41.317 --> 04:42.817
[chuckles] Colorful!

04:43.817 --> 04:46.900
[Goofy] A giant marsh-mellie!
Soft and squishy!

04:47.317 --> 04:50.567
[Mickey] And the Mystery Mouseketool!

04:52.692 --> 04:55.233
That's a surprise tool that can
help us later.

04:58.775 --> 05:01.233
♪ Toodles has the tools
The Mouseketools ♪

05:01.317 --> 05:04.275
♪ So when we need 'em
Toodles will bring 'em ♪

05:05.358 --> 05:08.233
He's here for meedles and youdles!
[laughs]

05:08.317 --> 05:10.567
And all we have to say is, "Oh, Toodles!"

05:11.275 --> 05:13.608
All we have to say is, "Oh, Toodles"

05:17.650 --> 05:20.233
OK, we've got our Mouseketools.

05:20.317 --> 05:24.358
Now let's help Donald
teach Donald Jr. their song and dance.

05:24.442 --> 05:25.442
[crashing]

05:25.525 --> 05:26.942
[Goofy] It's OK, everybody!

05:29.858 --> 05:31.067
Wahoo!

05:32.817 --> 05:34.775
I'm gonna practice my magic act!

05:35.025 --> 05:36.358
-[howls]
-[quacks]

05:36.567 --> 05:40.317
I will now make a beautiful rose appear.

05:40.942 --> 05:42.608
Hocus-pocus!

05:44.442 --> 05:47.025
Gosh! Is that a rose?

05:48.275 --> 05:49.442
Uh-uh.

05:53.108 --> 05:54.400
Nope... [laughs]

05:54.483 --> 05:56.067
Definitely not a rose.

05:56.275 --> 05:59.358
It's my polkie-dotted galosh,
and it's stinky!

05:59.733 --> 06:01.525
Just the way I like it!

06:01.608 --> 06:02.900
[laughing]

06:03.233 --> 06:05.275
Guess I ought to work on my act.

06:05.358 --> 06:08.775
[circus music]

06:08.858 --> 06:12.025
See you later at the show! Ee-hee!

06:12.275 --> 06:13.608
What a goof!

06:13.817 --> 06:16.858
[laughs]
I think Goofy's got the right idea.

06:16.942 --> 06:19.692
OK, Junior! We've got to practice!

06:20.733 --> 06:23.067
Step, step, step...

06:23.150 --> 06:24.525
Hold on, Donald!

06:24.608 --> 06:27.025
How about some music
to help us learn the dance?

06:27.650 --> 06:30.525
Hot dog! It's my ukulele!

06:31.067 --> 06:33.692
Oh, gosh, I haven't played it in a while.

06:38.608 --> 06:41.817
Uh-oh! Looks like I need a new string.

06:42.317 --> 06:45.942
Maybe Toodles has a Mouseketool
that can help me fix my ukulele.

06:46.358 --> 06:47.817
Everybody say...

06:47.900 --> 06:50.192
[sing-song] "Oh, Toodles!"

06:50.275 --> 06:52.525
[sing-song] Oh, Toodles!

06:53.483 --> 06:54.483
[bell ringing]

06:56.983 --> 06:58.692
Ready when you are, Mickey!

06:58.775 --> 06:59.900
[bell ringing] [laughs]

07:02.733 --> 07:06.067
[Mickey] We have the rescue truck,
a ball of yarn,

07:06.150 --> 07:09.983
a giant marshmallow,
and the Mystery Mouseketool.

07:10.358 --> 07:15.192
Hmm. Which Mouseketool can we use
to replace my ukulele string?

07:17.192 --> 07:18.650
The ball of yarn?

07:19.067 --> 07:22.483
Yep! We can use a piece of yarn
for the string!

07:23.400 --> 07:26.108
We've got ears. Say "Cheers!"

07:33.442 --> 07:34.733
Thanks, Handy Helper!

07:36.525 --> 07:38.233
-Ready, Donald?
-Yep!

07:38.317 --> 07:40.192
-Come on, Junior!
-Yeah!

07:40.317 --> 07:43.358
Step, step, step, step!

07:43.442 --> 07:46.275
Kick this way, kick that way.

07:46.358 --> 07:48.692
-[music blaring]
-[screaming] [sighs]

07:48.775 --> 07:50.275
Now what?

07:50.567 --> 07:51.567
[quacks]

07:52.192 --> 07:54.942
Gee, sounds like
something's going on outside.

07:56.525 --> 07:57.817
Let's go see!

08:03.192 --> 08:05.233
Hiya, boys! Give us a little room,

08:05.317 --> 08:07.942
because Daisy and I... and Hilda

08:08.025 --> 08:10.192
are gonna practice our roller-skating act!

08:10.733 --> 08:13.650
[chuckles]
Oh! One skating rink, coming up!

08:14.900 --> 08:15.900
Huh?

08:24.192 --> 08:27.275
♪ Skating around is lots of fun ♪

08:27.733 --> 08:30.192
♪ We'll disco skate until we're done ♪

08:31.858 --> 08:35.358
♪ Practicing twirls and fancy moves ♪

08:35.442 --> 08:38.317
♪ Roller skate with us
And feel the groove ♪

08:39.025 --> 08:40.192
♪ Come on, let's skate ♪

08:40.525 --> 08:43.150
♪ And make a perfect figure eight ♪

08:43.483 --> 08:46.483
[all] ♪ Ooh, la la, ooh, la la ♪

08:46.775 --> 08:50.442
♪ Oh now, let's skate an 'O'
A circle or a zero ♪

08:51.192 --> 08:54.400
[all] ♪ Ooh, la la, ooh, la la ♪

08:54.483 --> 08:58.233
♪ And then we'll be all done
Lined up like number one ♪

08:58.942 --> 09:04.942
[all] ♪ Ooh, la la, ooh, la la! ♪

09:06.692 --> 09:08.150
Oh!

09:09.650 --> 09:12.317
-Oh, boy, was that good!
-Yeah!

09:12.483 --> 09:15.858
Oh, goody, goody!
I guess you like our talent act.

09:15.942 --> 09:17.067
Uh-huh.

09:17.650 --> 09:21.275
Oh, what a sweet duckling!
What's your name?

09:21.608 --> 09:25.067
-We're calling him Donald Jr.!
-Uh-huh.

09:25.400 --> 09:28.317
And we're teaching him to dance and sing!

09:28.692 --> 09:33.400
[melodic quacks]

09:33.733 --> 09:38.525
Aw! I think Donald Jr.
wants to disco roller skate with us!

09:41.983 --> 09:43.525
Whoa!

09:43.817 --> 09:44.817
[laughing]

09:45.317 --> 09:47.775
Whoa! Be careful, little fella!

09:53.525 --> 09:54.567
[exclaiming]

09:57.650 --> 09:58.650
[quacks]

09:58.733 --> 10:00.317
-Ah!
-Junior!

10:00.858 --> 10:02.150
Whoa...!

10:02.608 --> 10:03.608
Whoa!

10:08.900 --> 10:12.192
Oh-ho-ho-ho-ho!

10:12.275 --> 10:14.067
-Here comes Hilda!
-Look out!

10:14.150 --> 10:15.650
Oh-ho-ho-ho-ho!

10:16.067 --> 10:19.317
-Yikes! Runaway hippo!
-[Hilda] Oh, oh, watch it!

10:20.108 --> 10:23.108
Oh, dear, we need something
to help us stop Hilda

10:23.192 --> 10:25.067
and give her a soft landing!

10:25.567 --> 10:26.983
We need a Mouseketool!

10:27.067 --> 10:28.650
Quick, everybody say,

10:28.733 --> 10:30.525
[sing-song] "Oh, Toodles!"

10:30.608 --> 10:32.358
[sing-song] Oh, Toodles!

10:34.358 --> 10:36.525
Hap-hap-happy to help you!

10:40.692 --> 10:44.192
[Minnie] We have the rescue truck,
a giant marshmallow,

10:44.275 --> 10:46.108
and the Mystery Mouseketool.

10:46.525 --> 10:48.900
Which Mouseketool can help us stop Hilda

10:48.983 --> 10:50.983
and give her a soft landing?

10:53.275 --> 10:55.275
[Daisy] The giant marshmallow!

10:55.733 --> 10:57.275
It's big enough to stop her,

10:57.358 --> 10:59.608
and it's soft and squishy to land on!

11:00.275 --> 11:03.067
[Mickey] We've got ears. Say "Cheers!"

11:08.442 --> 11:11.400
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

11:15.650 --> 11:18.775
Oh, oh-ho-ho! Oh-ho-ho!

11:19.567 --> 11:20.942
Oh! Oww!

11:22.900 --> 11:24.192
[quacking]

11:24.275 --> 11:26.567
-Hooray!
-Oh, good job, Donald!

11:26.650 --> 11:28.067
-Oh, goody, goody!
-[barking]

11:29.733 --> 11:32.525
Why does this always happen to me?

11:33.025 --> 11:34.733
We're off to practice more.

11:34.817 --> 11:36.858
Uh-huh. See you later at the show, boys!

11:38.817 --> 11:42.858
Time for us to practice, too.
Come on, let's dance!

11:44.942 --> 11:47.983
OK, Junior. Follow me!

11:49.733 --> 11:52.900
Step, step, step, step!

11:52.983 --> 11:55.817
Kick this way, kick that way!

11:55.900 --> 11:58.108
Spin and wiggle, wiggle, wiggle!

11:58.858 --> 12:01.983
Step, step, step, step!

12:02.067 --> 12:04.858
Kick this way, kick that way!

12:04.942 --> 12:06.608
Spin and...

12:08.275 --> 12:11.817
-Aw, phooey!
-[indistinct quacking]

12:12.108 --> 12:15.942
Gosh, fellas.
Learning takes time and lots of practice.

12:16.775 --> 12:19.525
Well, howdy, hi, hey, and hello to you!

12:19.900 --> 12:20.900
Hiya, Pete!

12:23.275 --> 12:26.067
Donald, have you shrunk?

12:26.400 --> 12:29.983
-That's not me, you big palooka!
-[quacks]

12:30.067 --> 12:32.608
-That's Donald Jr.
-[quacks]

12:33.983 --> 12:35.108
Whoa, yeah.

12:35.192 --> 12:37.650
I see the resemblance!
Plus you look alike.

12:37.983 --> 12:39.567
Aw, phooey.

12:39.650 --> 12:41.025
[quacks]

12:41.275 --> 12:43.900
So what talent are you
gonna show us today, Pete?

12:44.233 --> 12:46.442
Well, I've got a bunch
of different talents,

12:46.525 --> 12:49.567
but I don't know which one to do.

12:49.650 --> 12:51.900
Maybe you could help me decide!

12:52.650 --> 12:54.233
Oh, brother!

12:54.317 --> 12:56.358
Hey, Quackers, do me a favor, will you?

12:56.442 --> 13:00.150
Hold onto this and toss me
the bowling pins, if you please!

13:02.025 --> 13:04.983
Well, OK. Catch!

13:06.233 --> 13:09.983
♪ What a talented guy am I ♪

13:11.275 --> 13:14.942
♪ I can juggle while I sing
Oh, I can do most anything ♪

13:15.775 --> 13:17.817
♪ Just watch me, whoo-hoo! ♪

13:18.233 --> 13:21.442
♪ Play some spoons and my kazoo
There's nothin' I can't do ♪

13:24.817 --> 13:27.025
♪ Yes, I can juggle while I sing ♪

13:27.108 --> 13:28.775
♪ Oh, I can do most anything ♪

13:29.233 --> 13:31.733
♪ I can even do wild-bird calls ♪

13:32.275 --> 13:35.358
♪ Watch me call a moose
I mean, a goose ♪

13:35.442 --> 13:36.442
[laughs]

13:36.525 --> 13:38.192
Oh, specklebelly goose!

13:38.358 --> 13:41.192
Uh, honk, honk and quack, quack!

13:41.275 --> 13:43.108
And, well, look, here they come.

13:43.192 --> 13:47.775
[ducks quacking]

13:47.858 --> 13:51.983
Ooh, freckled feathers!
I must be losing my touch.

13:52.067 --> 13:54.608
[ducks quacking]

13:54.692 --> 13:57.775
All ducks and no specklebelly goose!

13:58.233 --> 14:00.525
-Well, I better go practice some more.
-[quacking]

14:01.025 --> 14:02.525
See you at the park!

14:02.858 --> 14:08.608
[blowing kazoo]

14:10.650 --> 14:14.192
Mickey, we've got to do something
with these ducks!

14:15.275 --> 14:19.025
Why don't we invite them to join us
for "Show Your Special Talent Day"?

14:19.608 --> 14:23.400
Hmm. We just need a place to keep them all
till we're ready.

14:23.483 --> 14:24.900
[barks]

14:27.983 --> 14:29.942
Good idea, Pluto!

14:31.817 --> 14:33.567
[ducks quacking]

14:33.650 --> 14:35.650
[Mickey]
The ducks can swim in your big washtub!

14:37.483 --> 14:39.650
Uh-oh! The tub's empty!

14:40.067 --> 14:41.775
We need to fill it up with water.

14:42.025 --> 14:43.817
Maybe a Mouseketool can help us!

14:44.025 --> 14:45.233
Everybody say,

14:45.317 --> 14:47.525
[sing-song] "Oh, Toodles!"

14:47.900 --> 14:50.650
[sing-song] Oh, Toodles!

14:55.608 --> 14:56.817
[Toodles laughs]

14:59.650 --> 15:02.525
[Mickey] OK, we've still got
the rescue truck

15:02.608 --> 15:04.942
and the Mystery Mouseketool.

15:05.192 --> 15:08.275
Which Mouseketool can we use
to fill up the tub with water?

15:10.483 --> 15:12.192
How about the rescue truck?

15:13.817 --> 15:17.733
Yeah. We can use the truck's fire hose
to fill the tub with water!

15:18.733 --> 15:21.483
We've got ears. Say "Cheers!"

15:35.983 --> 15:37.775
[quacking]

15:37.858 --> 15:40.358
There you go, duckies! [quacks]

15:40.817 --> 15:42.108
[Donald Jr. quacking]

15:42.192 --> 15:44.442
[quacking]

15:44.525 --> 15:48.108
[Mickey] Uh, Donald, I think Donald Jr.
wants to practice some more.

15:51.900 --> 15:55.192
OK now, Junior, take it from the top.

15:55.483 --> 15:58.775
Come on, let's all help Donald Jr.
do the dance steps!

15:59.150 --> 16:01.567
Stand up and dance with us!

16:02.483 --> 16:03.650
Ready?

16:09.567 --> 16:12.650
Step, step, step, step!

16:12.733 --> 16:15.567
Kick this way, kick that way!

16:15.650 --> 16:17.817
Spin and wiggle, wiggle, wiggle!

16:18.400 --> 16:22.192
Look, he's catching on!
Come on, let's do it again.

16:22.358 --> 16:24.733
-One more time!
-OK!

16:24.817 --> 16:27.692
[Mickey and Donald]
Step, step, step, step!

16:27.775 --> 16:30.567
Kick this way, kick that way!

16:30.650 --> 16:32.983
Spin and wiggle, wiggle, wiggle!

16:33.067 --> 16:34.525
-[Mickey laughs]
-[Pluto barks]

16:34.942 --> 16:37.567
[ducks quacking]

16:37.650 --> 16:38.692
Hey, hey!

16:38.858 --> 16:41.775
Everyone's at Mickey Park! Let's go!

16:42.067 --> 16:45.817
Oh, boy! It's time to show off
our special talents!

16:45.900 --> 16:50.733
[quacking]

16:53.942 --> 16:55.442
[microphone feedback]

16:55.525 --> 16:59.067
Oh! Ahem. Hello, everybody!

16:59.150 --> 17:03.483
Welcome to "Show Your Special Talent"!

17:04.025 --> 17:06.275
-Oh, goody, goody!
-Now you're talking!

17:06.358 --> 17:07.650
[all cheering]

17:07.733 --> 17:08.900
[Donald Jr. quacks]

17:10.400 --> 17:11.483
[quacks]

17:11.733 --> 17:13.858
Oh, how adorable!

17:14.692 --> 17:16.942
Raise the curtain, please!

17:17.275 --> 17:18.608
Okeydokey!

17:22.858 --> 17:24.775
Arh!

17:25.150 --> 17:27.275
Come on, come on!

17:27.692 --> 17:31.442
One curtain going up!

17:32.900 --> 17:34.900
-Oh, my!
-Oh, no!

17:34.983 --> 17:37.442
-Help!
-Get us down!

17:38.192 --> 17:40.692
Uh-oh! Hold on!

17:40.983 --> 17:42.567
Oh, my goodness!

17:42.650 --> 17:44.233
We need to get them down!

17:44.567 --> 17:46.817
Maybe there's a Mouseketool
that can help us!

17:46.900 --> 17:48.567
Quick! Everybody say,

17:48.775 --> 17:50.525
[sing-song] "Oh, Toodles!"

17:50.775 --> 17:52.608
[sing-song] Oh, Toodles!

17:53.983 --> 17:56.275
[Toodles] Here's T-T-Toodles!

17:56.733 --> 17:58.483
[laughs]

18:00.983 --> 18:03.775
[Mickey] All we have left
is the Mystery Mouseketool!

18:03.858 --> 18:08.400
Everybody say, "Mystery Mouseketool!"

18:08.483 --> 18:11.400
[all] Mystery Mouseketool!

18:12.192 --> 18:14.942
[Clarabelle]
And today's Mystery Mouseketool is...

18:15.400 --> 18:17.567
[gasps] ...the glove balloon!

18:17.983 --> 18:20.900
We can fly up in it
and bring the boys back down!

18:21.317 --> 18:22.900
Moo-arvelous!

18:23.358 --> 18:25.608
We've picked all our Mouseketools!

18:26.025 --> 18:28.483
Say, "super cheers!"

18:36.525 --> 18:39.483
Help me fly the glove balloon
to the top of the curtain.

18:39.775 --> 18:42.358
Grab the rope like this. Now pull!

18:43.775 --> 18:46.275
It's working! Keep pulling!

18:46.942 --> 18:49.442
Pull, pull, pull!

18:50.317 --> 18:52.942
Pull, pull, pull!

18:55.442 --> 19:00.400
-[quacking]
-Aw, I'm OK, Junior!

19:02.525 --> 19:04.067
Hold still! Whoa!

19:04.525 --> 19:05.567
Good work!

19:06.692 --> 19:07.942
Stupendous!

19:08.025 --> 19:09.775
What an entrance! [laughs]

19:10.275 --> 19:14.608
Now it's time
to "Show Your Special Talent"!

19:16.192 --> 19:17.317
Ahem.

19:20.525 --> 19:22.192
How'd she do that?

19:26.442 --> 19:27.858
[howls]

19:29.650 --> 19:32.192
Hocus pocus! A bunny!

19:39.442 --> 19:41.108
-[girls] Ooh, la la.
-[laughs]

19:44.567 --> 19:46.067
Honk, honk, honk!

19:46.150 --> 19:48.400
[goose honking]

19:48.483 --> 19:50.650
[gasps] A specklebelly goose!

19:50.733 --> 19:52.108
[applause]

19:52.192 --> 19:53.608
Oh, Petey!

19:54.400 --> 19:57.150
And now, without further ado,

19:57.233 --> 20:00.900
I present to you the talent
of all talents:

20:02.775 --> 20:05.983
Donald and Donald Jr.!

20:08.400 --> 20:11.400
OK, everybody, let's all stand up

20:12.567 --> 20:14.233
and get ready to dance.

20:14.358 --> 20:16.817
And this time, we're gonna sing, too!

20:17.192 --> 20:20.400
Come on! Dance and sing along with us!
Ready?

20:24.442 --> 20:27.733
♪ Step, step, step, step ♪

20:27.817 --> 20:30.483
♪ Kick this way, kick that way ♪

20:30.567 --> 20:32.983
♪ Spin and wiggle, wiggle, wiggle ♪

20:33.650 --> 20:36.400
♪ They go together like butter and jam ♪

20:36.483 --> 20:38.275
♪ Me and my Junior ♪

20:38.358 --> 20:39.608
[quacks in tune]

20:39.692 --> 20:42.233
♪ They're birds of a feather
Two's better than one ♪

20:42.442 --> 20:46.858
♪ That's me and my Junior ♪

20:46.942 --> 20:48.192
Let's do it again!

20:48.525 --> 20:51.608
♪ Step, step, step, step ♪

20:51.692 --> 20:54.525
♪ Kick this way, kick that way ♪

20:54.608 --> 20:56.900
♪ Spin and wiggle, wiggle, wiggle ♪

20:57.650 --> 21:00.400
♪ They go together like butter and jam ♪

21:00.483 --> 21:02.442
♪ Me and my Junior ♪

21:02.525 --> 21:03.567
[quacks in tune]

21:03.775 --> 21:06.275
♪ They're birds of a feather
Two's better than one ♪

21:06.733 --> 21:09.483
♪ Friends forever like Donald and me ♪

21:09.567 --> 21:11.400
♪ Me and my Junior ♪

21:11.483 --> 21:12.608
[quacks in tune]

21:12.733 --> 21:15.150
♪ Isn't it wow-wow-wow-whee ♪

21:15.483 --> 21:21.483
♪ That's Donald Jr. and me ♪

21:21.942 --> 21:23.567
[quacking]

21:24.025 --> 21:25.233
♪ Yeah ♪

21:26.483 --> 21:28.483
Moo-arvelous!

21:28.817 --> 21:31.150
Let's give them a big hand!

21:31.650 --> 21:33.608
[Goofy] Bravo!

21:33.692 --> 21:34.983
[cheering]

21:36.150 --> 21:37.608
Oh, Donald!

21:37.692 --> 21:40.483
You did a great job teaching Donald Jr.

21:40.567 --> 21:43.983
It must've taken a lot of practice
and patience to get it right!

21:45.067 --> 21:48.900
-Yep, it sure did!
-[quacking]

21:50.442 --> 21:54.942
Oh! Let's hear it for everybody
who joined us

21:55.025 --> 21:57.650
and showed their special talents today!

21:58.317 --> 22:00.483
Thanks for helping Donald and Donald Jr.

22:00.567 --> 22:02.608
practice their song and dance!

22:02.692 --> 22:03.733
[quacking]

22:03.817 --> 22:06.067
Yep! That's right, Junior!

22:06.150 --> 22:09.692
Come on, everybody! Let's all stand up

22:09.775 --> 22:11.817
and do the Hot Dog Dance!

22:18.900 --> 22:20.108
♪ Hot dog ♪

22:21.483 --> 22:22.900
[barking]

22:24.067 --> 22:25.275
♪ Hot dog ♪

22:29.275 --> 22:31.858
♪ Hot dog, hot dog, hot diggedy-dog ♪

22:31.942 --> 22:34.608
♪ Now, we got ears, it's time for cheers ♪

22:34.692 --> 22:38.775
♪ Hot dog, hot dog, the problem's solved ♪

22:39.192 --> 22:41.775
♪ Hot dog, hot dog, hot diggedy-dog ♪

22:43.025 --> 22:47.025
Teaching Donald Jr. how to dance,
so much fun.

22:47.483 --> 22:51.608
He's a great dancer, and so are you.
[quacks]

22:51.692 --> 22:53.817
What a hot dog day!

22:54.108 --> 22:56.567
♪ Hot dog, hot dog, hot diggedy-dog ♪

22:56.650 --> 22:59.192
♪ It's a brand-new day
Whatcha waiting for ♪

22:59.275 --> 23:03.733
♪ Get up, stretch out
Stomp on the floor ♪

23:03.817 --> 23:06.233
♪ Hot dog, hot dog, hot diggedy-dog ♪

23:06.483 --> 23:08.983
♪ Hot dog, hot dog, hot diggedy-dog ♪

23:09.067 --> 23:11.525
♪ We're splitting the scene
We're full of beans ♪

23:11.608 --> 23:14.817
♪ So long, for now from Mickey Mouse ♪

23:14.900 --> 23:16.192
That's me!

23:16.275 --> 23:22.275
♪ And the Mickey Mouse Clubhouse ♪

23:24.317 --> 23:26.400
Aw, thanks for stopping by!

23:28.733 --> 23:31.775
♪ Skating around is lots of fun ♪

23:32.275 --> 23:34.858
♪ We'll disco skate until we're done ♪

23:36.567 --> 23:39.817
♪ Practicing twirls and fancy moves ♪

23:39.900 --> 23:43.233
♪ Roller skate with us
And feel the groove ♪

23:43.567 --> 23:44.733
♪ Come on, let's skate ♪

23:44.817 --> 23:47.317
